heory.
=A0
Atma is like an ocean in which waves and rippes arise and move. =
Ocean does not get shattered when ripples hit each other and stays the same=
. But bodies, minds and other perishable objects arising in atma are like w=
aves and ripples arising and moving in ocean. They increase, decrease, get =
shattered etc. One identifying with the ocean of atma is beyond happiness a=
nd sadness. One identifying with the ripple of a body will experience happi=
ness, sadness etc.
=A0
Suppose one is watching a movie and knows that it is=
 not real and just a movie. Still, when a really scary scene comes, one may=
 be startled. Mere intellectual understanding that it is not real and just =
a movie, is not enough. It has to be ingrained fully in one's instincts. Si=
milarly, intellectually knowing that all this is a play and not real, is no=
t enough. When some really pleasurable and painful event happens, one WILL =
identify with the body and experience something.
=A0
If Shankara was fully =
enlightened before that episode (we don't know that for sure), then the act=
ion would not have bound him. Otherwise, it would've created a rina. If he =
experienced some pleasure, he would create a new rina to the queen, to vari=
ous deities (!) who live within one's consciousness and operate various par=
ts of one's body and mind, and to various beings in his virya who may have =
been significantly affected. He would have to pay those debts back later.
